<H3>2008-08-16</H3><A name=3D9206775130155270954>&nbsp;</A>=20
<H2>Steady, steady ...</H2>
<DIV class=3DblogPost>
<DIV style=3D"CLEAR: both"></DIV>
<P>
<DIV=20
style=3D"PADDING-BOTTOM: 0px; MARGIN: 0px; PADDING-LEFT: 0px; =
PADDING-RIGHT: 0px; DISPLAY: inline; PADDING-TOP: 0px"=20
id=3Dscid:0767317B-992E-4b12-91E0-4F059A8CECA8:b2784d30-9c47-4945-80ed-79=
1e48659b6a=20
class=3DwlWriterSmartContent>Technorati Tags: <A=20
href=3D"http://technorati.com/tags/nfoWorks" rel=3Dtag>nfoWorks</A>, <A=20
href=3D"http://technorati.com/tags/blogging" rel=3Dtag>blogging</A>, <A=20
href=3D"http://technorati.com/tags/Blogger" rel=3Dtag>Blogger</A>, <A=20
href=3D"http://technorati.com/tags/web%20site%20construction" =
rel=3Dtag>web site=20
construction</A></DIV>
<P></P>
<P>While I am preparing for major additions and starting my homework as =
a new=20
OASIS Open individual member, I am also performing some simple =
maintenance to=20
the site template (resulting in version 0.02):</P>
<UL>
  <LI>There is one bit of client-side JavaScript at the bottom of the =
template=20
  that is completely extraneous.&nbsp; Instead of adding a link to the =
blog's=20
  main page from archive pages, I made all blog pages have links to the =
main=20
  page from the blog title.&nbsp; There is no longer any=20
  JavaScript.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
  <LI>There were some typos in my modified header that I cleaned =
up.&nbsp; These=20
  included a double-word occurrence of "Jason" and a missing ":" after a =

  source-control label.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
  <LI>I moved the description to the sidebar in front of my =
profile.<BR>&nbsp;=20
  <LI>I made everything below the profile on the sidebar =
right-justified, as is=20
  my general preference.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
  <LI>I removed the dummy links that were in the original template, =
leaving the=20
  Google one for now.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
  <LI>I moved the blogger badge and the information about the RSS feed =
to the=20
  sidebar also.</LI></UL>
<P>The new template previews correctly.&nbsp; Making this post will =
apply it to=20
the main page, this individual post, and the archive page that this post =
is part=20
of.&nbsp; Older posts have not been republished.&nbsp; They will =
continue to be=20
formatted under the previous template, unless they are republished by me =
or as=20
the result of a comment.&nbsp; I also backed up the blog to my =
development=20
system before making the change on Blogger.</P>
<P>I believe there are extraneous cascading style-sheet (CSS) =
definitions in the=20
&lt;head&gt; section of the template, and I will distill it down=20
gradually.&nbsp; It is nice that there are no external style sheets, but =
I want=20
to simplify what is sent to the browser even more.</P>
<P>The development of the fire drill and incident-handling materials is =
going to=20
go slowly, and I will make more template changes when I need a respite =
from that=20
and from content-creation activities.</P>
