<H3>2008-08-15</H3><A name=3D3509386915766217145>&nbsp;</A>=20
<H2>IS 29500 (OOXML) Moving Ahead?</H2>
<DIV class=3DblogPost>
<DIV style=3D"CLEAR: both"></DIV>
<P></P>
<DIV=20
style=3D"PADDING-BOTTOM: 0px; MARGIN: 0px; PADDING-LEFT: 0px; =
PADDING-RIGHT: 0px; DISPLAY: inline; PADDING-TOP: 0px"=20
id=3Dscid:0767317B-992E-4b12-91E0-4F059A8CECA8:cca40607-b471-4a31-a5bc-06=
3a5a09d8aa=20
class=3DwlWriterSmartContent>Technorati Tags: <A=20
href=3D"http://technorati.com/tags/OOXML" rel=3Dtag>OOXML</A>, <A=20
href=3D"http://technorati.com/tags/IS%2029500" rel=3Dtag>IS 29500</A>, =
<A=20
href=3D"http://technorati.com/tags/ISO/IEC%20JTC1%20SC34" =
rel=3Dtag>ISO/IEC JTC1=20
SC34</A>, <A =
href=3D"http://technorati.com/tags/ODF-OOXML%20Harmonization"=20
rel=3Dtag>ODF-OOXML Harmonization</A>, <A=20
href=3D"http://technorati.com/tags/OpenDocument%20Format" =
rel=3Dtag>OpenDocument=20
Format</A>, <A href=3D"http://technorati.com/tags/OASIS%20ODF%20TC" =
rel=3Dtag>OASIS=20
ODF TC</A></DIV>
<P></P>
<H3>OOXML Struggling Over the Last ISO Hurdle?</H3>
<P>[a version of this entry appears on <A=20
href=3D"http://orcmid.com/BlunderDome/clueless/2008/08/nfoworks-is-29500-=
ooxml-moving-ahead.asp"><EM>Professor=20
von Clueless in the Blunder Dome</EM></A>]</P>
<P>Thanks to <A =
href=3D"http://ntouk.com/?view=3Dplink&amp;id=3D389">early word</A>=20
from Jerry Fishenden in the UK, we learn of today's <A=20
href=3D"http://www.iso.org/iso/pressrelease.htm?refid=3DRef1151">press =
release</A>=20
in Geneva: The appeals to acceptance of DIS 29500 (Office Open XML =
Formats) are=20
not sustained and preparation for publication of IS 29500 will =
proceed.&nbsp;=20
There is one caveat, and that is the prospect of an appeal over the =
appeal=20
resolution.&nbsp; </P>
<P>Meanwhile, DIS 29500 is now listed as deleted on the ISO site and we =
continue=20
to wait for release of the IS 29500 documents to the public.</P>
<P>It is difficult to be excited about any of this absent availability =
of a=20
specification to dig into.&nbsp; The maintenance process needs to get =
going and=20
it would be really great if this situation were completely resolved, =
with=20
publication of the edited IS 29500 specification, before the =
late-September=20
ISO/IEC JTC1 SC34 meeting in Korea.&nbsp; The wheels of JTC1 turn =
slowly, with=20
the best avenue for public input being the ECMA TC45 committee, where =
the gears=20
also turn slowly and mostly invisibly.&nbsp; There needs to be greater=20
transparency and public engagement, something that the federation system =
that=20
funnels down into JTC1 SC34 does not support.</P>
<H3>ODF as the R=C3=B4le Model</H3>
<P>The situation for ISO/IEC IS 26300 (Open Document Format 1.0) is not=20
particularly different, simply less encumbered at this point.&nbsp; =
Maintenance=20
is at the <A=20
href=3D"http://www.oasis-open.org/committees/tc_home.php?wg_abbrev=3Doffi=
ce">OASIS=20
Office Document TC</A>.&nbsp;&nbsp; It seems unlikely that substantial =
work on=20
ODF specifications will move elsewhere, given that this is where actual =
work is=20
being done, unencumbered by multi-national hierarchic process and =
governance=20
structures.</P>
<P>There are significant differences in transparency of OASIS =
maintenance in=20
contrast with ECMA's record so far.&nbsp; There is a <A=20
href=3D"http://www.oasis-open.org/committees/comments/index.php?wg_abbrev=
=3Doffice">publicly-usable</A>=20
and visible <A=20
href=3D"http://lists.oasis-open.org/archives/office-comment/">comment =
list</A> for=20
submissions and public archives of the <A=20
href=3D"http://lists.oasis-open.org/archives/office/">committee list</A> =
and <A=20
href=3D"http://www.oasis-open.org/committees/documents.php?wg_abbrev=3Dof=
fice">working=20
documents</A>, including a <A =
href=3D"http://wiki.oasis-open.org/office">wiki</A>=20
that provides access to all proposals for the under-development ODF 1.2=20
specification.&nbsp; There is also an <A=20
href=3D"http://lists.oasis-open.org/archives/oiic-formation-discuss/">ope=
n=20
discussion list</A> for the <A=20
href=3D"http://lists.oasis-open.org/archives/oiic-formation-discuss/20080=
6/msg00001.html">proposal</A>=20
of an ODF Interoperability and Conformance TC.&nbsp; The public notice =
and=20
review of that TC's chartering is expected soon.&nbsp; </P>
<P>Having joined OASIS as an individual, I expect to gain some very =
useful=20
practice in anticipation of similar provisions for OOXML.&nbsp; In many =
ways,=20
the division of my attention is going to be governed by where there is =
the least=20
friction in the way of open discussion, non-duplication of effort =
(through=20
knowing what comments there already are and knowing the views of =
others), and=20
ability to review and make proposals.&nbsp; It will be unfortunate if =
the only=20
open-to-the-public forum is <A=20
href=3D"http://idippedut.dk/post/2008/07/22/I-missed-you2c-Rob.aspx">a =
shadow</A>=20
created outside of any official OOXML maintenance bodies.</P>
<H3>Helpful Harmony</H3>
<P>The Harmony Principles and the development of nfoWorks appliances is=20
different from the maintenance of either specification and the creation =
of any=20
reference implementations and conformance/interoperability tools.&nbsp; =
But=20
there are clear opportunities for some cross-fertilization.&nbsp; I will =
gear up=20
for that in my usual pokey way.</P>
<P>Meanwhile, my attention is on the chartering of the ODF =
Interoperability and=20
Conformance TC, the under-review errata for ODF 1.0, and, um ..., =
getting this=20
blog in shape for easy, reliable use. </P>
