<H3>2008-08-13</H3><A name=3D465944466150478062>&nbsp;</A>=20
<H2>Weaving the Safety Net</H2>
<DIV class=3DblogPost>
<DIV style=3D"CLEAR: both"></DIV>
<P></P>
<DIV=20
style=3D"PADDING-BOTTOM: 0px; MARGIN: 0px; PADDING-LEFT: 0px; =
PADDING-RIGHT: 0px; DISPLAY: inline; PADDING-TOP: 0px"=20
id=3Dscid:0767317B-992E-4b12-91E0-4F059A8CECA8:33a32520-877c-4c33-a746-18=
a2c6a1035e=20
class=3DwlWriterSmartContent>Technorati Tags: <A=20
href=3D"http://technorati.com/tags/nfoWorks" rel=3Dtag>nfoWorks</A>, <A=20
href=3D"http://technorati.com/tags/blogging" rel=3Dtag>blogging</A>, <A=20
href=3D"http://technorati.com/tags/Blogger" rel=3Dtag>Blogger</A>, <A=20
href=3D"http://technorati.com/tags/web%20site%20construction" =
rel=3Dtag>web site=20
construction</A></DIV>
<P></P>
<P>The next series of activities for creation of this blog involve =
creation of a=20
safety net against my own slip-ups and as a defense in case the blog =
becomes=20
corrupted at some point.</P>
<P>This work takes up where <A=20
href=3D"http://nfoworks.org/diary/2008/08/ramping-up.htm">Ramping Up</A> =
has now=20
left off. Compulsive knot-hole peepers will find <A=20
href=3D"http://nfoworks.org/diary/construction.htm">a Construction =
Zone</A> and <A=20
href=3D"http://nfoworks.org/construction/2008/08/c080801.htm">Constructio=
n Notes=20
on "Pursuing Harmony" Blog Operation</A>.</P>
<P><STRONG>1. First steps 2008-08-13T23:10Z</STRONG>. The first step is =
to=20
capture the blog template and keep it in a form that is available under =
version=20
control any time it is necessary to restore an earlier template:</P>
<UL>
  <LI>I have switched from FTP to SFTP one more time, just to see if it =
is now=20
  working along with FTP (which took a while before it succeeded).=20
  <BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
  <LI>After accessing the Blogger dashboard for this blog, the original =
template=20
  is copied into the UTF-8 file default.htm.template.txt. That file is =
checked=20
  into the development folder for <A=20
  href=3D"http://nfoworks/diary">http://nfoWorks/diary</A> and placed =
under=20
  version control there. <BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
  <LI>Once we have this much we are ready for the next step. </LI></UL>
<P><STRONG>2. Template Cleanup 2008-08-14T00:11Z</STRONG>.&nbsp; The =
next step=20
is to clean up the template a slight amount in preparation for further=20
customization:</P>
<UL>
  <LI>The SFTP transfer is definitely not working.&nbsp; I reverted to =
FTP from=20
  Blogger to the <A=20
  href=3D"http://nfoworks.com/diary">http://nfoWorks.com/diary</A> =
directory on=20
  the hosted site.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
  <LI><A=20
  =
href=3D"http://nfoworks.org/diary/images/WeavingtheSafetyNet_E374/F08xx12=
200808131709BloggerTemplate.png"><IMG=20
  style=3D"MARGIN: 0px 0px 10px 10px"=20
  alt=3D"Browser View of Original Template (click for larger image)" =
align=3Dright=20
  =
src=3D"http://nfoworks.org/diary/images/WeavingtheSafetyNet_E374/F08xx122=
00808131709BloggerTemplate_thumb.png"=20
  width=3D216 height=3D240></A>The template is <A=20
  href=3D"http://nfoworks.org/diary/default.htm.template.txt">backed =
up</A>.&nbsp;=20
  If viewed in a browser, it may render as HTML&nbsp; rather than as =
text.&nbsp;=20
  Using the browser feature for viewing the page's source code will =
reveal the=20
  coded-HTML of the template.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
  <LI>The template is edited to add the following features:=20
  <UL>
    <LI>A !DOCTYPE directive is added to the top of the template, =
specifying=20
    HTML 4.01 Transitional, the prevailing format on this site.=20
    <LI>An HTML comment with version-control label is embedded in the =
page.=20
    <LI>A comment with up-to-date revision history is added to the end =
of the=20
    file.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp; </LI></UL>
  <LI>The text of the cleaned-up template is added to the Blogger =
account for=20
  use in all further posts (including the current version of this=20
  one).<BR>&nbsp; </LI></UL>
<P><STRONG>3. Safety Net Incorporation 2008-08-13T01:23Z</STRONG>.&nbsp; =
With a=20
maintainable template backed-up and versioned, there are many =
improvements=20
called for.&nbsp; Those are cosmetic and not urgent, however =
desirable.&nbsp;=20
Instead, provisions for locking down the blog, repairing/recovering it, =
and=20
restoring it to operation will be put in place.&nbsp; The arrangement =
depends on=20
the site being accessible by the administrator even though the blog is =
not=20
working properly for some reason.</P>
<UL>
  <LI><STRONG>default.firedrill.htm</STRONG> is a replacement for the =
blog=20
  default page when a fire-drill is being carried out (such as one we =
will have=20
  shortly, much like a boat drill carried out before leaving=20
  port).<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
  <LI><STRONG>default.quarantine.htm</STRONG> is a replacement for any =
page that=20
  is effectively quarantined until a remedy is available in its =
place.&nbsp;=20
  This is typically done as a new version of a blog archive page rather =
than as=20
  a replacement for the default page, although anything is=20
  possible.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
  <LI><STRONG>default.standby.htm</STRONG> is a replacement for the blog =
default=20
  page when the blog is made inaccessible for some reason.&nbsp; This is =
usually=20
  put up very quickly, without further details provided <U>until</U> =
later when=20
  there is some assessment of the situation.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
  <LI><STRONG>harmony-atom.standby.xml</STRONG> is a substitute for the =
blog's=20
  harmony-atom.xml and rss.xml Atom feed files when there is need to =
quarantines=20
  until a problem can be resolved.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
  <LI><STRONG>harmony-atom.testing.xml</STRONG> is a substitute for the =
two Atom=20
  feed files when the feed is blocked for a fire drill or other =
testing.</LI></UL>
<P>These pages are developed as part of the <EM>"Pursuing Harmony" Blog=20
Operations</EM> material.&nbsp; That's the next step.&nbsp; Then we can =
have our=20
first fire drill.</P>
<HR>

<P><SMALL>[<STRONG>update 2008-08-14T14:24Z</STRONG> added an important =
omitted=20
word.&nbsp; I'm now back on the out-of-sight work needed in order to =
perform a=20
successful fire drill.&nbsp; I forgot how tedious this is.&nbsp; The =
previous=20
setup on Orcmid's Lair is old and stale and needs to be refreshed as =
part of=20
that site's eventual repaving.&nbsp; Meanwhile, onward ... =
.]</SMALL></P>
