<H3>2008-08-12</H3><A name=3D4197879664481550814>&nbsp;</A>=20
<H2>Ramping Up</H2>
<DIV class=3DblogPost>
<DIV style=3D"CLEAR: both"></DIV>
<DIV=20
style=3D"PADDING-BOTTOM: 0px; MARGIN: 0px; PADDING-LEFT: 0px; =
PADDING-RIGHT: 0px; DISPLAY: inline; PADDING-TOP: 0px"=20
id=3Dscid:0767317B-992E-4b12-91E0-4F059A8CECA8:92115886-3d05-4d76-b64c-2d=
8276648e96=20
class=3DwlWriterSmartContent>Technorati Tags: <A=20
href=3D"http://technorati.com/tags/nfoWorks" rel=3Dtag>nfoWorks</A>, <A=20
href=3D"http://technorati.com/tags/blogging" rel=3Dtag>blogging</A>, <A=20
href=3D"http://technorati.com/tags/Blogger" rel=3Dtag>Blogger</A>, <A=20
href=3D"http://technorati.com/tags/web%20site%20construction" =
rel=3Dtag>web site=20
construction</A></DIV>
<P>This is an initial post for ramping up the Blogger creation of =
<EM>Pursuing=20
Harmony</EM>. The blog will replace the <A=20
href=3D"http://nfoworks.org/nfoDiary.htm">manually-created diary</A> =
that was=20
first used with <STRONG><EM><A=20
href=3D"http://nfoworks.org/">nfoWorks</A></EM></STRONG>. This initial =
page is=20
created to cause population of the blog, its archives, and the RSS feed. =
</P>
<P>The blog starts out using Jason Sutter's "Sand Dollars" format, one =
of the=20
supplied Blogger templates. I will customize that to achieve my =
preferred style=20
once operation of the blog is confirmed. </P>
<P>Customization happens after blog editing and posting is confirmed to =
be=20
functioning.</P>
<P>My first problem was attempting to use SFTP. I reverted back to =
plain-old FTP=20
to make sure the FTP log-in could succeed. This wasn't working the same =
as=20
previously, so I tried a different path name.&nbsp; The problem may have =
been a=20
lag in set-up of the account that I created for Blogger to use in =
posting to the=20
web site.&nbsp; After one false-start, it all started working.</P>
<P><STRONG>1.</STRONG> <STRONG>Update 2008-08-12T21:55Z</STRONG> After=20
succeeding with this initial post, I decided not to use the Blogger=20
NavBar.&nbsp; If I want to add a search panel for searching the blog =
and/or the=20
site, I will do that later.</P>
<P>On getting Windows Live Writer working with the site, I attempted to=20
establish an upload directory for images included in the blog.&nbsp; =
LiveWriter=20
reported that it could not confirm the URL.&nbsp; I will make sure the =
new=20
directory is established and give it a construction structure.&nbsp; I =
should=20
then be able to have LiveWriter use it.</P>
<P>I am also going to move the archive directory out of the top-level =
blog=20
directory, so that backup and maintenance is easier.&nbsp; </P>
<P>Live Writer reminded me to add tags to this post, and I will do that =
now=20
too.&nbsp; I see that the categories work differently and are =
independent of=20
tags.&nbsp; I must not be so careless in choosing categories.</P>
<P><STRONG>2.</STRONG> <STRONG>Update 2008-08-12T23:34Z</STRONG> The =
archive is=20
moved and the image directory was pre-populated with an index.htm so =
that Live=20
Writer's concern for the folder was removed.&nbsp; It is now time to =
demonstrate=20
that picture uploading works:</P>
<P align=3Dcenter><A title=3D"Neighborhood Rose (click for larger =
image)"=20
href=3D"http://nfoworks.org/diary/images/RampingUp_D13A/F070903a.jpg"><IM=
G=20
src=3D"http://nfoworks.org/diary/images/RampingUp_D13A/F070903a_thumb.jpg=
"></A>=20
</P>
<P align=3Dleft><STRONG>3.</STRONG> <STRONG>Update =
2008-08-13T00:03Z</STRONG>=20
After I figured out what time it is here (for adjusting to GMT in these =
little=20
update items), I also managed to correct the URL for where the images =
are so=20
that, not only are they uploaded, they are also correctly-reachable from =
the=20
blog post.</P>
<P align=3Dleft>My next effort is to make sure that I have a back-up =
procedure for=20
mirroring the blog content on my development machine along with the =
other parts=20
of <STRONG><EM>nfoWorks</EM></STRONG>.</P>
<P align=3Dleft>After that has concluded, I will need to start working =
on the=20
template.</P>
<P align=3Dleft><IMG style=3D"MARGIN: 0px 0px 10px 10px" border=3D0=20
alt=3D"Simon's American cousin, the romantic Edwin" align=3Dright=20
src=3D"http://nfoworks.org/diary/images/RampingUp_D13A/Templar20040816.pn=
g"=20
width=3D262 height=3D377> <STRONG>4.</STRONG> <STRONG>Update=20
2008-08-13T00:12Z</STRONG> Well, the Neighborhood Rose images are on the =
blog=20
site, but Live Writer fails to notice that I corrected the URL in my FTP =

settings.&nbsp; So I am linking in the above picture manually.&nbsp; I =
will=20
introduce an additional image so that it can upload with the new =
settings.</P>
<P align=3Dleft>Now I can introduce the backup procedure and then start =
adjusting=20
the template.</P>
<P align=3Dleft><STRONG>5. Update 2008-08-13T00:53Z</STRONG> One concern =
I had is=20
the automatic creation of subfolders to hold images from separate =
posts.&nbsp; I=20
have verified that no subfolder index is available on the server and =
there is no=20
way to explore the images but via image elements on the blog =
pages.&nbsp; That=20
is satisfactory.</P>
<P align=3Dleft><STRONG>6.</STRONG> <STRONG>Update =
2008-08-13T20:25Z</STRONG> I=20
have carried out one manual backup.&nbsp; Before taking the =
customization to the=20
next level, I have made a couple of simple touch-ups.&nbsp; </P>
<UL>
  <LI>
  <DIV align=3Dleft>The title is changed from "Pursuing Harmony" to =
"nfoWorks:=20
  Pursuing Harmony."<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp; </DIV>
  <LI>
  <DIV align=3Dleft>The little e-mail option down near the comments and =
links line=20
  after each blog is removed.&nbsp; The e-mail content is so ugly, =
devoid of=20
  formatting and any images, that I prefer people use other means off of =
the RSS=20
  feed or by using their browser to clip and forward =
pages.</DIV></LI></UL>
<P align=3Dleft>The next step is to construct the safety net and =
fire-drill=20
procedure for the blog.&nbsp; It has been some time since a blog has =
been=20
corrupted, but that is no reason to start operating without a net.</P>
